  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Livestock Mobility through the Optimization of Cross-Border and Local Consultation Frameworks and the Delivery of Assistance in Time of COVID-19</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project creates the conditions for strengthened local dialogues between stranded transhumant herders due to COVID-19 mobility restrictions at the borders between Niger, Nigeria, Benin and Burkina Faso, host populations and relevant authorities. This is done through data collection, cross-border local negotiation and local consultation frameworks, in order to achieve a consensus on the regulation of access to natural resources, as well as on the implementation of measures to support and secure the return of transhumance herders to their areas of destination of their choice.</narrative>
  </description>
